gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 114, 76ers 105
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks rally from down 12, outscore the 76ers, 34-22 in the 4th quarter to lift them for a 114-105 win. Giannis Antetokounmpo led the way with 32 points, 11 rebounds and seven assists for the Bucks, while Brook Lopez (19 points, seven rebounds, five assists, five 3PM) and Damian Lillard (17 points, nine assists) added a combined 36 points in the victory. Tyrese Maxey tallied a team-high 30 points and five 3PM for the 76ers in the losing effort. The Bucks improve to 43-24 on the season, while the 76ers fall to 36-30.
